  "body": "# 🐞 Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nQuantstamp reported:\r\n> In beacon-chain/sync/pending_blocks_queue.go, function sortedPendingSlots returns  []int. Slot indexes, which are stored in the returned array, are uint64 values, but are converted to int when appended to the returning array : append(slots, int(s)) (see L147). Thus, an overflow may occur. \r\n\r\nSince slots are `uint64` everywhere, to prevent possible overflow, and for consistency - we should return `[]uint64` from the method. Add corresponding test.\r\n\r\n**NB: Take the opportunity and review the code for integer overflows all over the place.**\r\n\r\n## 🔥 Error\r\n\r\nPossible overflow.",
